  "description": "<p>\n\t1.Bad companies are destroyed by crisis, Good companies survive them, Great companies are improved by them.<span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Andy Grove, Intel Co-founder</span></p>\n<p>\n\t坏的公司被危机打败，好的公司渡过危机，优秀的公司因危机而更好。<span>&mdash;</span>安迪&middot;葛洛夫 (英特尔共同创办人)</p>\n<p>\n\t2.Pain and suffering are always inevitable for a large intelligence and a deep heart. The really great men must, I think, have great sadness on Earth.<span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Fyodor Dostoyevsky, Writer</span></p>\n<p>\n\t痛跟苦难对智慧与心量的养成，是无可避免的。那些真正伟大的人，我觉得，一定都有很难受的经历。<span>&mdash;</span>费奥多尔‧陀思妥耶夫斯基 (作家)</p>\n<p>\n\t3.A cynic is a blackguard whose faulty vision sees things as they are, and not as they ought to be.<span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Ambrose Bierce, Writer</span></p>\n<p>\n\t讽世者是无赖，其不当的观点只看见事情的样貌，而不是它应该成为的样子。<span>&mdash;</span>安布罗斯&middot;比尔斯 (作家)</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">4.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">I like the dreams of the future better than the history of the past.</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">T. Jefferson&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">我不缅怀过去的历史，而致力于未来的梦想。</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">杰弗逊（美国第3任总统）&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">5.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">A great man is always willing to be little.</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">R. W. Emerson</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">伟大的人物总是愿意当小人物的。</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">爱默生</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">6.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Life is just a series of trying to make up your mind.</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">T. Fuller</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">生活只是由一系列下决心的努力所构成。</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">富勒&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">7 .</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">I have nothing to offer but blood, boil, tears and sweat.&nbsp;</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Winston Churchill, British politician &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">我能奉献的没有其它，只有热血、辛劳、眼泪与汗水。&nbsp;</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">英国政治家 丘吉尔</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">8.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Dare and the world always yields. lf it beats you sometimes, dare it again and again and it will succumb.&nbsp;</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">W. M . Thackeray. British novelist &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">大胆挑战，世界总会让步。如果有时候你被它打败了，不断地挑战，它总会屈服的。</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">英国小说家 萨克雷</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">9.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">And gladly would learn , and gladly teach .</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Chaucer , British poet</span></p>\n<div>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">勤于学习的人才能乐意施教。</span><span>&mdash;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">英国诗人, 乔叟</span></div><br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p776364/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p776364\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p776004/\">BBC：2016年度最佳食物摄影 你看饿了么？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p776058/\">2016奥巴马白宫记者晚宴演讲：33分钟段子机</a></li><li s